Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world... Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world for you who seek freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stretches out right before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.01,0:00:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your endless dreams are your guide,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.01,0:00:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,surpass them, under the flag of your beliefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.19,0:00:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.20,0:00:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.71,0:01:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the summer sun\Nsways the sails of my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.82,0:01:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cue to open the door to a new world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.33,0:01:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sailing through the rocky waves of despair
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.34,0:01:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We head beyond the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.01,0:01:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.68,0:01:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.19,0:01:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.36,0:01:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.07,0:01:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Steer for the Clouds! Capture the South Bird!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.68,0:02:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you need to tell us, old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.38,0:02:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. I'll start by telling you\Neverything I know about the sky island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.72,0:02:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of it's certain, but it's up to you\Nif you wanna believe it or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.33,0:02:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yeah! We believe you!\N--Geez, you're fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.56,0:02:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a strange phenomenon\Nthat occurs in these waters--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.40,0:02:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sometimes it'll turn to night,\Neven though it's the middle of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.90,0:02:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We saw that! Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.91,0:02:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Night came, and then\Nsome monsters appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.41,0:02:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The giants?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.78,0:02:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a story about where they\Ncome from, but forget 'em for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.49,0:02:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sudden nightfall...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.92,0:02:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's caused by the shadows\Nof extremely compact clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.36,0:02:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean cumulonimbus clouds?\NBut it was too dark to be clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.87,0:02:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! You're so dumb, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.20,0:02:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It gets cloudy on days\Nwhen there's lots of clouds!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.44,0:03:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yeah! Cloudy!\N--Cloudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.67,0:03:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.87,0:03:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are clouds known as\N"cumuloregalis clouds."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.34,0:03:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They pile high into the sky but\Nproduce no air currents or rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.75,0:03:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When they appear high in the sky,\Neven sunlight is blocked out,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.22,0:03:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,bringing afternoon "nighttime" to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One theory has it that cumuloregalis\Nclouds are fossilized clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.46,0:03:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that have floated in the sky for\Nthousands and thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.73,0:03:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous! Clouds with no\Nair currents even after building up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're free to believe they can't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not asking you to believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.38,0:03:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're mystery clouds, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.48,0:03:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty much. There's still\Nno explanation for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.62,0:03:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're awesome, Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.25,0:03:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. If a sky island really does exist...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.35,0:03:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that'd be the only possible place!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Gotcha! Let's go above those clouds!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.03,0:03:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Get up, Zoro!\N--Huh? Is it morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.36,0:03:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready, everyone! Cloud rudder full!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.40,0:04:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for filling us in, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.53,0:04:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I gotta say\Nwe don't know how to get there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now comes the real problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.27,0:04:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me start by saying this...\NPut your lives on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.24,0:04:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're already near death...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.24,0:04:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Knock-Up Stream is a\Ncurrent that shoots into the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.01,0:04:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can theoretically take it\Ninto the sky. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.32,0:04:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a current that can send ships flying, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.02,0:04:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Then it just needs to\Nsend us above the clouds!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On a current?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.30,0:04:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But wouldn't we just end up\Nsmashing back into the ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.57,0:04:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, yeah. The key is timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy to talk about\Nbeing sent up the current,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's not gonna be as nice\Na trip as you guys think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.82,0:04:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Knock-Up Stream is a natural disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.09,0:04:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something that should\Nnormally be avoided!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.86,0:05:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How exactly does a water\Ncurrent rise into the sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.26,0:05:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've never heard of\Nanything like that before...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.70,0:05:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.74,0:05:15.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we can only guess as to\Nhow that monstrous current works.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.84,0:05:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one's dumb enough to\Njump in and find out, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.81,0:05:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The accepted theory goes like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.55,0:05:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deep beneath the sea floor,\Nthere are large cavities,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.92,0:05:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and low-temperature\Nsea water seeps into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The heat from the earth below\Nturns that water into steam,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.93,0:05:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the resulting pressure causes\Nan explosion on the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.33,0:05:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One big enough to send the sea flying\Nand create a current into the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.81,0:05:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For about one minute, the sea\Ncontinues to rise into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.71,0:05:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One minute?! What size of explosion\Nare we talking about here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:05:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The explosions change location each time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.78,0:06:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and occur five times a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.32,0:06:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to be blown into smithereens...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, y'know,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.09,0:06:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,describing a grand natural phenomenon\Nwith words and logic is foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So, basically, we gotta ride this current\Nthat only appears five times a month
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.37,0:06:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and hope the sky island shows up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. And if you miss, you'll fall\Nback down, slam into the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.38,0:06:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and then you'll all end up\Nat the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.72,0:06:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Alright! Let's give up on the sky island!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.79,0:06:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.63,0:06:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta have the luckiest luck\Nthat's ever lucked to make it there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fine! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.44,0:06:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.70,0:06:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We'll be fine"? How can you say\Nsuch groundless stuff so easily...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.64,0:06:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, just look at the Going Merry now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.74,0:07:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks so pitiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't stand up to a\Ngigantic disaster like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.95,0:07:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. Even in mint condition,\Nthat ship wouldn't stand a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.66,0:07:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speed, weight, strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.96,0:07:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That boat'd be blasted apart in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.06,0:07:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... See! It really is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.53,0:07:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't you worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.84,0:07:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have Masira and Shojo\Nhelp take you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.44,0:07:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only after we strengthen your ship, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.54,0:07:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Just leave it to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.84,0:07:34.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.51,0:07:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't even ask us...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Do you even understand?!\N--Understand what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For starters... Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.59,0:07:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most we can stay on\Nthis island is one more day!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, the Log Pose will\Nstart pointing to the next island!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.80,0:07:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Yeah! We won't make it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.00,0:07:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, old man! You're not a psychic!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.60,0:07:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt you know,\Nbut how many days will it be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.87,0:08:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until the Knock-Up Stream and\Nthe cumuloregalis clouds line up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.84,0:08:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! How many months?!\NNo, how many years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.85,0:08:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow afternoon.\NIf you're going, you better get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.15,0:08:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't make it in that time!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? If you don't like it, then just quit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.46,0:08:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.19,0:08:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't right! We just met you today!\NAren't you being too nice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.50,0:08:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hold on, Usopp!\N--Shut up, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.20,0:08:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow just happens\Nto be the perfect chance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.01,0:08:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to go to this legendary,\Nunknown "sky island"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.68,0:08:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll help strengthen\Nour ship and take us there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's way too convenient!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.52,0:08:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly are you scheming?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.92,0:08:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus you're Noland the Liar's\Ndescendant! We can't trust you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.29,0:08:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old-timer! Dinner's ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.53,0:09:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.67,0:09:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami-san! Dinner's--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.70,0:09:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?! Are you gonna fight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.91,0:09:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever "midday night"\Nis confirmed in Masira's turf,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.08,0:09:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,cumuloregalis clouds appear in\Nthe southern skies the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.92,0:09:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And judging from its five-per-month rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.02,0:09:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Knock-Up Stream will\Nprobably be active tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.69,0:09:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll happen somewhere south of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.63,0:09:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a 100% certainty, but there's\Na good chance it'll be tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.14,0:09:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to have met fools like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.28,0:09:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's go and have some food!\NTake it easy at my place today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...comrades!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.62,0:09:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Food! Hurry, Usopp!\N--Yeah! C'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.72,0:10:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Chopper! Go get Robin-chan!\N--Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.66,0:10:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like all we can do is try\Nour best to get into the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.20,0:10:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though in the end, it's up to luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.37,0:10:13.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami. Am I miserable and cowardly?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.91,0:10:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You forgot "stupid."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.77,0:10:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how you feel. Now go apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.88,0:10:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.38,0:10:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?! Yuck! Don't wipe your snot on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.26,0:10:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's booze is especially great!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.43,0:10:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat up, eat up! The saury full\Ncourse is just getting started!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.97,0:10:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.67,0:10:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha, salvage bum!\NThat's a Tabasco Bomber!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you! Long-nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.91,0:10:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Girlie! Come sit here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.74,0:10:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 100 years too early to\Nhave Nami-san wait on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.32,0:11:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I saw gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in the skull's right eye!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.19,0:11:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.40,0:11:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That tear-soaked sentence was\Nthe last thing Noland wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.90,0:11:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I saw gold in the skull's right eye..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.91,0:11:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland was executed that same day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.98,0:11:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after coming to Jaya,\Nthose words make no sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.01,0:11:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The skull's right eye..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.82,0:11:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it referring to the name\Nof a city that once existed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.95,0:11:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or was it an allusion to his own death?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.72,0:11:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blank pages that follow say nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.96,0:11:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why we dive!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.03,0:11:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a dream! On the sea floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.73,0:11:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.74,0:11:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not if you keep eating like that, we won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.08,0:12:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotten quite late, but I see it, Bellamy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.75,0:12:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to go ashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.15,0:12:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream-chasing fools deserve\Nmore than a few lumps!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.14,0:12:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The day I arrived on Jaya.\NEntry for May 21, 1122."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.91,0:12:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland! Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.35,0:12:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Upon landing on the island,\Nwe heard strange bird calls
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.32,0:12:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the sound of a very large\Nbell coming from the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.02,0:12:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound from that huge\Ngold bell resonated far and wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.53,0:12:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,almost as if showing off the\Nprosperity of a city long past!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.57,0:13:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought we knew everything\Nafter living for a few decades..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.04,0:13:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland! Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.51,0:13:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...but experiencing the transience\Nof this civilization that flourished
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for a long time on the wide\Nopen sea left us speechless!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.28,0:13:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound of the bell had\Nus stopped in our tracks!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.56,0:13:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland's so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! A giant gold bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.80,0:13:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, old guy!\NYou like Noland after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.47,0:13:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Look at this!\N--Wow! Gold bells!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.24,0:13:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how exactly are those "giant"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These aren't that bell.\NThey're bell-shaped ingots.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.11,0:13:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found these three on the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.12,0:13:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ingots?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.18,0:13:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! So there really is a city of gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.52,0:13:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't prove that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.19,0:13:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could find that much gold in any old ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.46,0:13:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it does prove that there\Nwas a civilization in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ingots are made to have standardized weights.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.40,0:14:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means they were used for trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.00,0:14:08.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And the strange bird calls\Nmentioned before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.87,0:14:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Masira!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.14,0:14:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Whoa! There's more?!\N--This one's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.98,0:14:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That's all of 'em.\N--Wow! It's so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.45,0:14:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold bells and a bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.48,0:14:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose they were symbols of old Jaya?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.62,0:14:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno, but I think they were\Npart of some sort of model.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.93,0:14:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This here's called a South Bird,\Nand they still exist on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.40,0:14:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Do they have weird calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.60,0:14:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. Just like the logbook says!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.87,0:14:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sailors have long used South Birds to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.44,0:14:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.05,0:14:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad! You guys! Go into\Nthe forest! The southern forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.02,0:14:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! What're you talking about?!\NAre you crazy, old guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:14:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go catch this bird! Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.42,0:14:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! What for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.92,0:15:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we need a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.36,0:15:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen closely! The Knock-Up Stream\Nyou're heading for tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.36,0:15:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is located directly south of this cape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.43,0:15:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you going to get there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.60,0:15:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just sail straight there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.87,0:15:14.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Grand Line, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.94,0:15:18.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're on the open sea,\Nthere's no way to get your bearings!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.41,0:15:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.04,0:15:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading for ocean, not an island,\Nso we have no guide to rely on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.68,0:15:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how do we go straight south?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.65,0:15:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You use that bird's behavior!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.42,0:15:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some types of animals have\Naccurate, internal magnets
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which allow them to get their bearings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're lower than an animal, Zoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like you're anyone to talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,South Birds are the greatest of such animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.61,0:15:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how vast the land\Nor sea they're thrown into,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.71,0:15:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their bodies will always indicate\Nthe direction accurately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.25,0:16:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, without one of these birds,\Nyou're going nowhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't even get the\Nchance to go to the sky island!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.05,0:16:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you telling us this now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit fussing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.36,0:16:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time! Hurry! Don't dilly-dally!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.60,0:16:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to go into the forest\Nin the middle of the night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.23,0:16:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You forgot these!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna get started on your beat-up ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.11,0:16:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it,\Nthere was no time to be partyin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.38,0:16:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again, why are you telling us this now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.68,0:16:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! Make sure you catch at\Nleast one South Bird before dawn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.55,0:16:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's pitch dark!\N--Quit pulling me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.42,0:16:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault! My hands\Nare moving on their own!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My stomach's so full...\NI don't think I can chase birds...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.30,0:16:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are these weird birds?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.73,0:16:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just catch one so we\Ncan get back to drinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.74,0:16:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did we wind up doing this so suddenly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.71,0:17:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--You're in the way!\N--Man! Couldn't he have told us during the day?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.05,0:17:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are the birds?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.21,0:17:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we knew where they were,\Nwe wouldn't be out looking for 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.05,0:17:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our only clue is that they have a weird call...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.39,0:17:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they look just like that gold statue...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.42,0:17:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there really such dumb-looking birds?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.73,0:17:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus "weird call" is way too vague!\NHow're we supposed to know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.00,0:17:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said we'd know once we're in the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.24,0:17:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A weird call!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.67,0:17:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.01,0:17:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.07,0:17:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we got no other choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.28,0:17:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have three nets. Let's split\Ninto three groups and search!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.08,0:17:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.08,0:17:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! Let's beat up those weird birds!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.25,0:17:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.46,0:17:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! Whatever we run into,\NI'll protect you, Nami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.83,0:17:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sanji-kun! What about me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.46,0:17:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell if I care! Quit being insecure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.07,0:17:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let's catch a bird\Nso we can get out of this forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.07,0:18:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start by listening closely\Nfor that bird we heard earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.41,0:18:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That bird call!\N--Jooo! Come out! Joooo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.01,0:18:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.12,0:18:13.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you catching me for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.92,0:18:17.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Nami! That's a cool thing\Nyou got on! Where'd you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.39,0:18:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.16,0:18:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spider!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's just a spider!\NYou poor thing... Come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.20,0:18:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spiders are yucky, you moron!\NToss it away somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.07,0:18:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get away, Usopp! I bet it's poisonous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.67,0:18:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're falling from the trees!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.77,0:18:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is too gross!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.64,0:18:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably a species of tarantula!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.11,0:18:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! They won't spit poison\Nas long as we don't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to fight spiders a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.12,0:18:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you can count me out when\Nit comes to creepy bugs like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.39,0:18:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here! I totally hate them!\NTotally! Hurry and throw it far away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.19,0:19:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? But those moths and\Ncentipedes don't bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.51,0:19:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate moths and centipedes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.11,0:19:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh! Don't leave me behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.65,0:19:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear screams...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.35,0:19:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A centipede, huh? It's pretty damn big...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not nice to kill everything. Poor thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.69,0:19:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it gets for trying to attack me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.30,0:19:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--But...\N--What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.37,0:19:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the path we just took here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.44,0:19:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bird call... This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.71,0:19:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out for that quagmire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.75,0:19:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait for--!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.25,0:19:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.59,0:19:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Chopper! It's an Atlas!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.79,0:19:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Atlas?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.79,0:20:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup! Atlases and Hercules are\Nthe most admired bugs in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.19,0:20:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Beetles?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.23,0:20:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You never heard of 'em?!\NThey're super hard to catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.30,0:20:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is better, them or the One Piece?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.47,0:20:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... That's hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.80,0:20:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy! There's something here, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.21,0:20:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! It's a Miyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.78,0:20:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.61,0:20:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It flew away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.61,0:20:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.42,0:20:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After it! Don't let it get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.42,0:20:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A beehive! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.74,0:20:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this forest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.94,0:20:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Luffy! Look there!\N--It's that bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.58,0:20:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He dropped the beehives!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.38,0:20:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Eh?!\N--Huh? Did he say something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.55,0:21:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "I'll kill you for invading this forest!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.53,0:21:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, boy! Don't be making us mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.50,0:21:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not nice to suddenly show up\Nat night and demand gold, kiddos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.51,0:21:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave! We got work to do now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.71,0:21:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're bodyguards, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.55,0:21:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, there was\Na pirate named Cricket...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.05,0:21:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the sad tale of your\NMontblanc family at the pub.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.79,0:21:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It moved me so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.72,0:21:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure someone else struggled to\Nget has a special flavor all its own!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.63,0:21:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna know what people call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.07,0:21:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hyena!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.20,0:22:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, beyond the never-ending sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.31,0:22:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The future that I once saw\Nis now starting to take shape
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.66,0:22:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are days where I almost lose to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.17,0:22:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happened, there was\Nsomeplace warm I could go
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.55,0:22:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The friends I took pride in\Nalways, without fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.69,0:22:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pushed me onwards, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.70,0:23:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the stars are pouring\Ndown underneath the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.97,0:23:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This unique moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.35,0:23:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old guy! We caught a bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.18,0:23:14.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What happened, old diamond-head?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.45,0:23:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing we could do! We're pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.82,0:23:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gold's been stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.66,0:23:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! Forget about that junk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.09,0:23:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellamy's mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.50,0:23:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back by morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.16,0:23:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.50,0:23:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dreams Don't Come True?!\NBellamy versus the Saruyama Alliance"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.80,0:23:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.14,0:23:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
